Ford Motor Co &lt;F> is to invest 23 mln stgin high technology equipment at its Bridgend engine plant inSouth Wales, the Press Association said.    The move includes a new computerised engine test facilitywhich the company says will make the factory one of the mostefficient of its kind in the world.    Bridgend currently supplies Escort, Orion and some Fiestaengines to Ford plants in Britain, West Germany and Spain. Reuter&#3;